Summarize this conversation per instructions:

Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "You pause just inside the threshold of the Ruined Chapel, letting your eyes sweep across the shadow-cloaked sanctuary. Along both walls, you spot a handful of rusted iron sconces affixed at intervals, some still holding long-dead torches and the cracked stubs of old candles. Near the altar, a larger candelabrum lies toppled among broken pews, its holders warped but a few half-melted candles remain.\n\nThough no flames flicker here now, these sconces and candelabra could certainly hold fire--if you wished, you might try to set a torch alight or coax a stubborn candle to life and push back the darkness. The lingering gloom presses close, but you sense that even the faintest spark might reveal more than just the architecture.\n\nWhat would you like to do?"
}

Player: Dungeon Master Note: Current date and time: 1492 Ches 2 01:57:00. Player: I light a couple sconces

Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "You pull a torch from your pack and strike a spark, coaxing it to life with practiced hands. Using its steady flame, you move along the cracked flagstones, igniting the remnants of two old sconces--one on the northern wall and another near the shattered stained glass. The ancient candles sputter before catching, their flames guttering blue-white as if struggling against the oppressive gloom.\n\nAs the flickering light spreads, the eerie prismatic patterns from the broken windows shift and dance across the ruined pews and the desecrated altar. For a moment, you notice shadows on the far side of the chapel moving not in accordance with your torchlight, but as if slithering away from it. The cold in the room deepens, and the ghostly hymns echo a little louder, as if your intrusion has not gone unnoticed.\n\nSuddenly, you catch a flicker of movement: a patch of darkness near the toppled candelabrum seems to grow denser, elongating into a formless, living shadow. It glides silently toward you, drawn to the warmth and light you have kindled.\n\nA chill runs down your spine--your presence, and the light, have awakened something lurking in the gloom.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "createEncounter",
      "parameters": {
        "player": "Norn",
        "npcs": [],
        "monsters": ["Shadow"],
        "encounterSummary": "Norn's lighting of the chapel sconces has drawn the attention of a lurking Shadow, which now emerges from the darkness to attack in the Ruined Chapel."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

Player: Combat Summary: {
  "narration": "With a precise strike, your sword cuts through the Shadow's insubstantial form. Your total attack roll of 19 hits its armor class of 12, allowing you to deal 9 points of damage. The Shadow, clutching its fading essence, is overcome by your blow. Its dark form dissipates into wisps of darkness, vanishing completely. The Ruined Chapel falls silent once more, the threat finally ended. You have gained 100 experience points from defeating this foe, the shadows no longer lurking here to threaten you.",
  "combat_round": 1,
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateEncounter",
      "parameters": {
