        "changes": "Norn gains 100 experience points for defeating the Shadow."
      }
    },
    {
      "action": "exit",
      "parameters": {}
    }
  ]
}

Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "Your sword cleaves through the Shadow, and its form unravels into dusk and mist, vanishing as if it had never existed. The unnatural chill in the Ruined Chapel begins to fade, and for a long moment, only the soft crackle of your torch and the sputtering sconces can be heard.\n\nAs the last vestiges of the Shadow disappear, a silence settles over the ruined sanctuary. Prismatic reflections from the shattered windows shimmer more peacefully, and the ghostly hymns recede, replaced by an almost expectant hush. It seems the chapel itself breathes easier, as if grateful for your victory.\n\nYou feel the weight of the darkness lift from your shoulders, and a subtle warmth--faint, but real--returns to the air. The echoes of your battle drift away, leaving you alone with the chapel's long-held secrets. You have gained 100 experience points for vanquishing the lurking Shadow.\n\nWith the threat ended, you have a chance to catch your breath and investigate further among the toppled pews, desecrated altar, and the strange spiral stains marking the floor. Somewhere within these ruins, clues to Elen's fate and the keep's curse may yet be found.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateCharacterInfo",
      "parameters": {
        "characterName": "Norn",
        "changes": "Increased experience points from 6321 to 6421 after defeating the Shadow."
      }
    }
  ]
}

Player: Dungeon Master Note: Current date and time: 1492 Ches 2 01:58:00. Player: I need to leave the game for a bit

Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "You take one last look around the quiet, haunted chapel. The flicker of the sconces casts long, gentle shadows; the prismatic remnants of stained glass glimmer faintly on the ruined stone. For now, the darkness seems to have receded, offering you a rare, peaceful respite in these cursed halls.\n\nYou gather your belongings and steady your breath, knowing the secrets of Shadowfall Keep will wait for your return. As you step back from your vigil, a faint, reassuring warmth settles around you--a promise that your hard-won ground in the chapel will remain safe until you're ready to resume your quest.\n\nRest easy, Norn. When you next return, the mysteries and dangers of the keep will await you, unchanged.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "exitGame",
      "parameters": {}
    }
  ]
}

Player: Dungeon Master Note: Resume the game, the player has returned.

Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "You stand once more within the Ruined Chapel of Shadowfall Keep. The sconces you lit earlier still flicker weakly, casting trembling shadows across toppled pews, shattered stained glass, and the scarred altar at the far end. The air is thick with memory: the silence is deeper, broken only by the faint echo of ghostly hymns on the edge of hearing.\n\nYour last battle with the Shadow lingers in your mind, but for now the danger seems to have passed. The cold gloom presses close, and the spiral stains on the floor draw your attention back to the desecrated altar. Somewhere in these haunted ruins, answers to Elen's fate and the keep's ancient curse may yet be uncovered.\n\nWhat would you like to do?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

