Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "You move with care through the cold, broken pews and shifting patterns of colored light. The Ruined Chapel is heavy with secrets, and as you begin to comb the chamber, the silence deepens. The flickering sconces illuminate toppled benches, shattered glass, and desecrated relics. Your eyes linger on the spiral stains trailing toward the altar, and the faint echo of a hymn seems to guide your steps.\n\nAs you examine the room, you notice a faint movement at the periphery of your vision: a translucent, sorrowful figure in tattered vestments stands near the altar, his face etched with grief. This is surely Father Aldren, the spirit of the old chaplain, who watches you with mournful, pleading eyes. He raises a trembling hand and gestures toward the altar, but no words escape his lips.\n\nIf you wish to search for hidden compartments, clues, or items, you will need to make an Investigation check. Please roll a d20 and add your Investigation modifier.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 5
      }
    }
  ]
}

