Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "With a final, determined blow, your weapon slices through the ghostly armor of the vengeful specter. The spirit utters a hollow, echoing cry--caught between anguish and relief--before dissolving into fading wisps of shadow and pale blue light. The unnatural chill that once gripped the chapel fades, leaving in its wake an almost peaceful warmth. \n\nThe broken altar stands before you, bathed in the wavering glow cast by your torch and the sconces you lit earlier. The silence now feels less oppressive, as if the ancient burdens here have lifted. At your side, the sorrowful spirit of Father Aldren lingers, eyes bright with gratitude and hope. He gestures once more, this time with less urgency, beckoning you to the altar.\n\nYou stand victorious, the chapel momentarily safe. What would you like to do next?",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
        "timeEstimate": 2
      }
    }
  ]
}

Player: Dungeon Master Note: Current date and time: 1492 Ches 2 02:07:00. Player: how much expereince did I get defeatign the spectre?

Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "You pause at the altar, catching your breath after the fierce confrontation. In the stillness that follows, you reflect on your victory over the vengeful specter. Though defeating such a formidable spirit would typically grant valuable experience, you recall the unnatural nature of this haunting: the challenge here was not only martial, but bound to the lingering curse and Father Aldren's plight. \n\nAs the specter's essence faded, you felt the keep's oppressive gloom lighten, but you also sensed that this particular fight served more as a release of old pain than a true conquest. No experience points are awarded for this encounter--the reward is the peace restored, and the opportunity to uncover the chapel's secrets with Father Aldren's guidance.",
  "actions": []
}

Player: Dungeon Master Note: Current date and time: 1492 Ches 2 02:07:00. Player: I need to leave the game for a bit

Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "You step away from the altar, the hush of the Ruined Chapel pressing gently around you. The battle-worn stones and flickering candlelight bear silent witness to your recent struggles, but now, for the moment, peace lingers where shadows once prowled. Father Aldren's spirit remains near, watching with silent gratitude, as if promising to guard the chapel until you return.\n\nYou gather your things and take one last look at the prismatic light spilling across the ruined pews. The secrets of Shadowfall Keep will wait. When you return, your place in this story will be exactly as you left it--and the answers you seek will still be here, just beyond reach.\n\nRest well, Norn. The next chapter of your adventure in the keep will wait for your return.",
  "actions": [
