Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "You kneel among the spiral stains and sift through the debris with a practiced eye, your mind still buzzing from victory. The pale light from the sconces flickers across your shoulder as you run your hand along the fractured altar, searching for inconsistencies in the stonework or signs of a hidden panel.\n\nYour efforts are rewarded: your fingers find a narrow seam concealed beneath a layer of dust and old wax. With a gentle press, a section of the altar shifts, revealing a cleverly hidden compartment. Inside, you find a small silver key engraved with a sunburst, its surface untarnished by time. Next to it rests a worn chaplain's journal, its cover marked with the symbol of the chapel, and a vial of blessed water that glimmers with an inner light. Tucked into the corner is a holy symbol of silver, its design unbroken, and a heart-shaped amulet crafted from darkened silver--its surface warm to the touch.\n\nA torn piece of blue cloak and a slip of parchment, hastily tucked inside the journal, confirm that Scout Elen was here and learned of the knight's heart. The journal's first page is open to a hurried entry: \"The relic must not fall to shadow. Only the heart can shield one from the knight's curse.\"\n\nAs you take in these discoveries, Father Aldren's spirit bows his head in gratitude, gesturing for you to take the heart-shaped amulet--a beacon of hope and a vital defense against the darkest sorcery within the keep.\n\nWhat will you do with these treasures, Norn?",
