Dungeon Master: {
  "narration": "You cradle the knight's heart amulet in your palm, its silver surface gleaming softly in the wavering candlelight. The amulet is heavier than it looks, shaped like a stylized heart, expertly crafted and adorned with delicate filigree reminiscent of both sunbursts and the crest of old Harrow's Hollow. A faint warmth pulses from its core, as if the metal contains a living memory.\n\nExamining the back, you notice an inscription, barely visible: \"To hold this heart is to hold my resolve. Let no darkness claim what I have sworn to protect.\" Embedded in the center of the amulet, beneath a glassy cabochon, is a single crimson droplet -- likely a drop of blood, preserved by some ancient magic. The edges of the amulet hum with warding energy, and as you grip it, you feel a subtle shield settle over your spirit, steadying your resolve against fear and despair.\n\nYou recall the chaplain's journal: \"Only the heart can shield one from the knight's curse.\" It seems certain this relic is key to surviving Sir Garran's presence deeper within the keep, and perhaps to breaking the curse that binds so many restless dead.\n\nAs you look up, Father Aldren's spirit nods solemnly, and the air shimmers with a sense of blessing. In your hand, the amulet feels like hope made solid.",
  "actions": [
    {
      "action": "updateTime",
      "parameters": {
